# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Source-code packages accidentally matched by the broad `models/` (line ~52) and
# `state/` (line ~192) rules above. These are Python SOURCE, not artifacts. Without
# these negations a fresh clone/checkout is missing src/forecasting/models and
# src/core/state, which breaks the entire `src` package on import. Fixed 2026-07-03.
!src/forecasting/models/
!src/forecasting/models/**
!src/models/
!src/models/**
!services/inference_api/models/
!services/inference_api/models/**
!src/core/state/
!src/core/state/**
# ...but never track compiled artifacts inside those re-included source packages.
src/forecasting/models/**/__pycache__/
src/models/**/__pycache__/
src/core/state/**/__pycache__/

# ============================================================================
# Regenerable artifacts — kept locally, out of git.
# Curated analyses now live tracked under docs/analysis/.
# SACRED (stay tracked, used to restore DB tables on service startup):
#   - seeds/latest/*, data/backups/seeds/*, data/backups/*.csv.gz|*.sql.gz
#   - data/backups/features/* (news/analysis/H5/asset tables — news history is NOT regenerable)
#   - data/pipeline/04_cleaning/output/* (MACRO_DAILY_CLEAN + 9 MASTER files)
#   - usdcop-trading-dashboard/public/data/** + public/forecasting/** (operator 2026-07-09:
#     todo lo que sirve el dashboard viaja en git; los DAGs son refresh, no bootstrap)
# ============================================================================

# Runtime output dirs (pipelines recreate these on each run)
